About us¬†
We are an award winning, national $16B public offer industry fund focused on the education and community sectors. Working for NGS Super means being part of something bigger and working to make a difference to our members and their financial future. ¬†

Our people are key to our success, and as we expand, we‚Äôre committed to finding and retaining the right talent to take on the journey. ¬†As well as a flexible and fun workplace, we offer competitive benefits including additional leave entitlements, personal & professional development and health & wellbeing programs.

Click on the video below to learn more!¬†

The Role¬†
We‚Äôre looking for an AI Engineer to join our newly formed Engineering team in Sydney in a 12 month fixed-term role. ¬†Reporting to the Head of Engineering, you will play a critical role in designing, developing, and deploying advanced AI solutions that directly support the data-driven decision-making needs of NGS Super‚Äôs Investment Team.¬†

Your focus will be partnering with the Investment Team to build scalable, secure, and high-performance AI/ML models that optimise investment strategies and product decisions, and contribute to the architecture and delivery of intelligent systems that integrate seamlessly with the Fund‚Äôs broader technology ecosystem.

What you‚Äôll do

Design, develop and deploy scalable AI/ML models to support investment modelling, forecasting, and optimisation activities.
Collaborate closely with the Investments Team to translate complex financial and data requirements into robust AI solutions.
Build and maintain intelligent systems that integrate with existing backend services, data pipelines, and cloud infrastructure.
Apply advanced techniques in natural language processing, graph-based modelling, and supervised/unsupervised learning.
Develop and maintain secure, production-grade AI workloads using cloud-native tools and infrastructure-as-code practices.
Maintain strong documentation of all design decisions, procedures, and playbooks.
Participate in code reviews, testing, and incident response to ensure quality and maintainability of AI systems.
Work collaboratively with cross-functional teams including Data Engineers, Backend Developers, and Cloud Engineers to support end-to-end delivery.
Stay current with emerging AI technologies and recommend improvements or new approaches.

About you¬†

An analytical and solutions-focused technical engineer, you will bring the following key skills:
Demonstrated experience designing and deploying AI/ML models in production environments, specifically AWS.
Strong proficiency in machine learning frameworks and libraries (e.g. TensorFlow, PyTorch, Scikit-learn).
Experience with natural language processing, graph-based modelling, and deep learning techniques.
Solid understanding of data engineering principles and integration with backend systems.
Familiarity with cloud-native development, infrastructure-as-code and CI/CD practices.
Strong programming skills in Python and/or other relevant languages.
Proven ability to translate complex business requirements into technical AI solutions.
Commitment to secure coding practices and compliance with data governance standards.
Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
Effective communication and collaboration skills across technical and non-technical teams.

The following are nice to have but not essential:

Experience working in an APRA-regulated or similar financial services environment.
Exposure to cloud platforms such as AWS and Azure, including AI/ML services.
Familiarity with MLOps practices and tools for model lifecycle management.
Knowledge of financial modelling or investment analytics.
Relevant certifications in AI/ML, cloud technologies, or data science.

If you are looking for a long-term contract where you can make an impact in a period of growth and technical transformation, we would love to hear from you.

We are a super fund that has an exceptional work culture, provides a diverse offering in developing our people and you can be a part of it while earning an attractive remuneration package!¬†

Interested and suitably qualified candidates should submit a copy of their updated CV.¬†

Please note that to be eligible for this role, you are required to have permanent Australian working rights and residency.¬†

We are an equal opportunity employer committed to creating a workplace that values diversity, equity, and respect for all individuals.

How do we teach thinking in the age of commoditized intelligence?¬†


Our Australia-based AI-first Ed-Tech is solving this!

Mission-driven Ed-Tech sector leader

LLM / NLP / AI production systems

Sydney Head office / hybrid / remote

Decades-long university partnerships / established market player

An exciting opportunity now exists to join one of the fastest growing and most innovative companies in the dynamic education technology sector - Studiosity.

Now reaching over 1.8 million students across the UK, USA, Canada, Australia, NZ, UAE and beyond ‚Äì Studiosity is the premium partner of choice amongst educational institutions.

This makes us uniquely positioned to win and keep growing our mission to be able to enable better learning experiences and equal opportunity for students.




What you will do

Reporting to the Head of AI, you will join our Product Platform team as an experienced AI Engineer, leading the experimentation, design and development of market-leading generative AI education solutions. Your work will directly support our mission to improve life chances for students everywhere.

This role places you at the forefront of defining how the next generation learns - inventing new ways for students to interact with knowledge, practice skills, and receive personalised feedback.

A critical part of your work will be evolving our AI guardrails and quality systems, ensuring that all AI-generated feedback is safe, ethical, pedagogically sound, and supporting learning outcomes. Our AI team works closely with our Academic Standards team to ensure we focus on the high educational standards. You‚Äôll help shape not only the product experience, but also the principles and practices that underpin responsible AI in education.




About you

You are an experienced AI Engineer with strong foundations in machine learning, software engineering, and modern generative AI techniques.¬†

You will ideally have:

3+ years of experience designing, building, and operating scalable AI pipelines across data collection, evaluation, deployment, and monitoring.

2+ years of commercial experience working on NLP, large language models, or document understanding/analysis applications.

Strong understanding of machine learning fundamentals, model evaluation, data preprocessing, and robust software engineering practices.

Experience developing intelligent search systems and/or anomaly detection algorithms is a plus.¬†

Experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, GCP, or Azure) and associated AI/ML services.

A demonstrated ability and enthusiasm for mentoring and guiding engineers, fostering growth and technical excellence across the team.

Demonstrated active use of modern AI tools in the development process is expected.¬†

Experienced with Python.




Why Studiosity?

Studiosity is an amazing place to work: In addition to our noble purpose of increasing life chances for students, we benefit from a low ego, non-corporate and lifestyle-friendly work ethic and culture. These are complemented by an exceptional passion and drive for lifelong learning in which everyone stays results-driven and proud of the work we deliver every day.


To express your interest please forward a cover letter accompanied by your current resume. Thanks for your consideration and we look forward to hearing from you.

Ad Text:
Title:

Expression of Interest ‚Äì Systems Modeller (Digital Engineering)

About KBR:

At KBR ‚Äì We do things that matter.¬†

We deliver science, technology and engineering solutions to governments and companies around the world. KBR employs approximately 38,000 people worldwide with customers in more than 80 countries and operations in over 29 countries.¬†

KBR is proud to work with its customers across the globe to provide technology, value-added services, and long-term operations and maintenance services to ensure consistent delivery with predictable results. At KBR, We Deliver.¬†

Think.KBR.com

KBR in Australia¬†

With over 65 years working on some of Australia‚Äôs largest and most complex projects, KBR has unmatched experience supporting the nation‚Äôs critical infrastructure, energy transition and national security priorities. KBR has around 2,000 employees throughout Australia, who are focused on delivering innovative technology and engineering solutions for a safer, more secure and sustainable future.

Belong, Connect and Grow at KBR¬†

At KBR, we are passionate about our people and our Zero Harm culture. These inform all that we do and are at the heart of our commitment to, and ongoing journey toward being a People First company. That commitment is central to our team of team‚Äôs philosophy and fosters an environment where everyone can Belong, Connect and Grow. We Deliver ‚Äì Together.

The Opportunity

KBR is executing a Digital Engineering strategy to manage complexity, leverage technical capability, and deliver speed to capability for Defence. This strategy includes enabling digital engineering environments and facilities, as well as executing Defence programs to develop, host, and integrate systems as models, architectures, or digital twins.

We are seeking Expressions of Interest from experienced Systems Modellers to play a key role in driving modelling and simulation activities for major Defence technology programs, including C4ISREW, SATCOM, Space, Air Defence, and other critical capabilities.

Role Overview

As a Systems Modeller, you will:

Capture and model concepts, requirements, and designs for complex Defence programs.

Perform Mission Engineering using mission threads and scenarios to support modelling in the customer problem space.

Develop and sustain MBSE architectures using tools such as CATIA Cameo, Enterprise Architect, AFSIM, or ANSYS.

Ensure integration and traceability across lifecycle phases, from requirements through to verification.

Contribute to the growth and enablement of Digital Engineering Infrastructure, including the Systems Integration Laboratory and virtual collaboration environments.

Responsibilities

The key responsibilities of the role will include, but are not limited to:

Develop and integrate mission engineering models and simulations using MBSE tools.

Define end-to-end architecture solutions aligned with technology standards and roadmaps.

Collaborate to mature capability enablement through environment design, model development, and reporting.

Validate and integrate externally sourced models into system or enterprise frameworks.

Enhance KBR‚Äôs Digital Engineering knowledge base through reusable artefacts and configuration scripts.

Engage with Defence clients, project teams, and industry partners to define architecture strategies.

Manage configuration and databases for digital engineering toolchains.

Ensure compliance with Defence standards and cybersecurity protocols.

Deliver technical documentation and reporting on modelling activities.

Qualifications, Skills and Experience

Essential:

Degree in Systems Engineering, Computer Science, or related field.

5+ years‚Äô experience in digital systems design and integration.

Proven experience in systems architecture development within Defence or regulated environments.

Strong proficiency in MBSE methodologies and tools (SysML, UML).

Eligibility for Australian Government Security Clearance (NV1 or higher).

Desirable:

Postgraduate qualifications and professional recognition (CPEng, ACS).

Experience in innovation, capability development, and Agile/SAFe frameworks.

Familiarity with DevOps, coding languages (Python, JavaScript), and secure systems design.

Benefits of KBR

A workplace culture certified as a Great Place To Work (Aus, India, UK & US)

Job Title: Research Scientist, Vision Language and Multimodal Modeling
Ad Text:
At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google‚Äôs technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan for more information.

Minimum qualifications:

PhD degree in Computer Science, a related field, or equivalent practical experience.
One or more scientific publication submissions for conferences, journals, or public repositories (such as CVPR, ICCV, NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR, etc.).
Preferred qualifications:

Experience in areas like face anti-spoofing, biometrics, 3D/2.5D vision, facial landmark/pose estimation.
Experience with TensorFlow, Flume, common computer vision libraries/frameworks and Android.

Interest to build production systems.

Excellent software engineering skills (e.g., C++, python, data processing, production backend development, etc.).
About the job


As an organization, Google maintains a portfolio of research projects driven by fundamental research, new product innovation, product contribution and infrastructure goals, while providing individuals and teams the freedom to emphasize specific types of work. As a Research Scientist, you'll setup large-scale tests and deploy promising ideas quickly and broadly, managing deadlines and deliverables while applying the latest theories to develop new and improved products, processes, or technologies. From creating experiments and prototyping implementations to designing new architectures, our research scientists work on real-world problems that span the breadth of computer science, such as machine (and deep) learning, data mining, natural language processing, hardware and software performance analysis, improving compilers for mobile platforms, as well as core search and much more.

As a Research Scientist, you'll also actively contribute to the wider research community by sharing and publishing your findings, with ideas inspired by internal projects as well as from collaborations with research programs at partner universities and technical institutes all over the world.

In this role, you will develop models and architectures grounded in foundation models, data-efficient algorithms, and federated learning.

Responsibilities

Author research papers to share and generate impact of research results across the team and in the research community.

Help in growing research business across teams by sharing research trends and best practices within the community.

Define the data structure, framework, design, and evaluation metrics for research solution development and implementation under minimal guidance. Identify timelines and obtain resources needed.

Identify new and upcoming research areas by interacting with external and internal collaborators. Help in developing research strategy and plans to expand the impact of Google research with some guidance.
Contribute to conducting experiments based on the research question. Develop research prototypes or conduct simulations to further evaluate the impact of research, finalize hypotheses, and refine the research methodology under minimal guidance.
